		Comment <a href="#c_1713650623">17</a> by John
		posted on 6/23/2006 at 4:12 PM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>If anyone is actually interested in a historical/legend based mud that is unintentionally, but truly, educational, then you should look up Legend MUD.  All of the realms are based either on what actually existed in history or (more often) what people thought existed at a moment in history.  The game is divided into three separate eras: ancient, medieval and modern.  Travel within an era is by foot, horse or boat, and the geography is similar to an abridged map of the world.  Travel between eras is accomplished through simple time travel quests.  If someone were to come up with a successful graphical version of this premise, it would be a boon to people's knowledge of real life history, legend and myth.  As it is, it's a fun game to play even without pictures.  :)</p></div>
